category=Advanced Concepts
description=<p>Revolution allows you to print a complex layout by specifying how screen areas are positioned and scaled on the printed page.  This tutorial walks you through the process.</p>
duration=9:57
filename=layout_printing.avi
level=3
licensed=true
name=Layout Printing
scripts=<p>Scripts Used in this Tutorial:</p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">on mouseUp</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  hide me</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  open printing with dialog</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  set the width of this stack to item 1 of the printPaperSize</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  set the width of stack &quot;header&quot; to item 1 of the printPaperSize</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put the height of stack &quot;header&quot; into tLogoHeight</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put the width of stack &quot;header&quot; into tLogoWidth</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  print card 1 of stack &quot;header&quot; into \\</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">    rect 0,0,tLogoWidth,tLogoHeight</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  print card 1 of this stack into rect \\</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">    0,tLogoHeight,tLogoWidth,tLogoHeight+the height of this stack</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  close printing</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  show me</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">end mouseUp</font></p>\n<p></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">on mouseUp</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  hide me</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  open printing with dialog</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  set the width of this stack to item 1 of the printPaperSize</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  set the width of stack &quot;header&quot; to item 1 of the printPaperSize</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put the height of stack &quot;header&quot; into tLogoHeight</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put the width of stack &quot;header&quot; into tLogoWidth</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  print card 1 of stack &quot;header&quot; into \\</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">    rect 0,0,tLogoWidth,tLogoHeight</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put 14,8 into tPrintFrom1</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put 342,98 into tPrintFrom2</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  put 82,102,518,234 into tPrintToRect</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  add tLogoHeight to item 2 of tPrintToRect</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  add tLogoHeight to item 4 of tPrintToRect</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  print card 1 of this stack from tPrintFrom1 to tPrintFrom2 \\</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">    into rect tPrintToRect</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  close printing</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">  show me</font></p>\n<p><font face="Courier New" size="12" color="#000000">end mouseUp</font></p>
title=Layout printing: creating a custom printing solution.
topics=<p>Key Topics Covered in this Tutorial:</p>\n<p>-&#9;How to print a layout</p>\n<p>-&#9;How to scale portions of a card onto a printout</p>